## 3. Enum Value Registry

### OOB Authentication Methods

Hierarchical, weakest to strongest:

| Value | Description |
|---|---|
| `session_only` | No OOB required. Guardian signs based on existing agent session. |
| `email_confirmation` | Confirmation sent to registered email. |
| `sms_otp` | One-time password sent via SMS. |
| `totp` | Time-based one-time password (e.g., authenticator app). |
| `device_signature` | Cryptographic signature from user's registered device. Assumed default OOB method. |
| `biometric` | Biometric verification on user's device. |
| `hardware_key` | Purpose-built security hardware. |

Custom methods are permitted and should follow `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`. The hierarchy is extensible; services and guardians declare where custom methods sit in the ordering.

### Protocol Error Codes

| Code | Description |
|---|---|
| `UNS_ATTESTATION_LEVEL_MISMATCH` | Guardian's provided attestation level does not meet the level required by the Gateway. See [`UNS_ATTESTATION_LEVEL_MISMATCH`](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md) in the error catalog. |
| `UNS_SIGNATURE_INVALID` | A signature in the chain failed verification. |
| `UNS_NONCE_EXPIRED` | Challenge nonce expired before handshake completed. |
| `UNS_NONCE_REPLAY` | Previously used nonce detected; potential replay attack. |
| `UNS_SERVICE_NOT_REGISTERED` | Agent attempted handshake for unregistered service. |
| `UNS_GUARDIAN_UNREACHABLE` | Gateway could not contact Guardian. |
| `UNS_HANDSHAKE_TIMEOUT` | User did not respond to OOB authentication within timeout window. |
| `UNS_USER_DECLINED` | User explicitly denied OOB authentication request. |
| `UNS_OOB_FAILED` | Out-of-band authentication delivery or completion failed. See [`UNS_OOB_FAILED`](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md) in the error catalog. |
| `UNS_MANIFEST_CHANGED` | Service manifest updated since Guardian last cached it. |
| `UNS_MANIFEST_SIGNATURE_INVALID` | Service manifest signature verification failed. See [`UNS_MANIFEST_SIGNATURE_INVALID`](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md) in the error catalog. |
| `UNS_SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | Gateway temporarily unable to process requests. |

### Coordination Node Status

| Value | Description |
|---|---|
| `active` | Gateway/Guardian is operational and accepting requests. |
| `maintenance` | Temporarily unavailable for scheduled maintenance. |
| `deprecated` | Scheduled for removal; clients should migrate. |

### Deprecated Enum Values

The following values appeared in earlier specification drafts and must not be used in new specifications. They are listed here for migration reference only.

`SINGLE_LOCK`, `DOUBLE_LOCK`, `TRIPLE_LOCK`, `QUAD_LOCK` — Replaced by per-request attestation levels. Every UNS authentication is trilateral; the "lock" tier model has been eliminated.

`REQUESTED`, `PENDING`, `ACTIVE`, `CONSUMED`, `EXPIRED`, `REVOKED` — Token states from a pre-issued token model. Replaced by the challenge-response nonce model where the token is progressively enriched during the handshake, not pre-issued and state-tracked.

`ESCALATION_REQUIRED`, `RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED`, `SPENDING_LIMIT_EXCEEDED`, `TOKEN_INVALID`, `TOKEN_EXPIRED`, `TOKEN_REVOKED` — Replaced by the updated protocol error codes above.

