### 4.2 Node Identity Variables

Shared across all three node types (Guardian, Gateway, Coordination Node). These appear in node registration, the Coordination Node registry, and challenge/receipt payloads.

<details>
<summary><code>node_id</code> — string — Unique DID-format identifier for any UNS node.</summary>

**Required.** Format: `did:uns:{role}:{name}` (e.g., `did:uns:gateway:acme`, `did:uns:guardian:alice`). Used in Coordination Node registry lookups, challenge tokens, and receipt payloads. Immutable once registered.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md), [coordination_node_initial_api_specification.md](../specs/coordination_node_initial_api_specification.md), [cryptographic_operations_specification.md](../specs/cryptographic_operations_specification.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>gateway_id</code> — string — Identifier of a specific Gateway.</summary>

**Required.** DID-format identifier (e.g., `did:uns:gateway:acme`). Included by the Gateway in the challenge token and appears in the receipt. Also used as a lookup key in the Coordination Node registry.

**Sources:** [gateway_role.md](../specs/gateway_role.md), [gateway_infrastructure.md](../specs/gateway_infrastructure.md) (D1 receipts, services), [receipt_format_and_assembly_specification.md](../specs/receipt_format_and_assembly_specification.md), [mcp_tool_definitions.md](../specs/mcp_tool_definitions.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>guardian_id</code> — string — Identifier of a specific Guardian.</summary>

**Required.** DID-format identifier (e.g., `did:uns:guardian:alice`). Registered with the Coordination Node at onboarding. Appears in receipt payloads and is used for Guardian discovery and key verification.

**Sources:** [guardian_role.md](../specs/guardian_role.md), [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 receipts), [gateway_infrastructure.md](../specs/gateway_infrastructure.md) (D1 receipts), [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)

