<summary><code>public_key</code> — string — Institutional signing key for a Gateway or Guardian.</summary>

**Required.** Hex-encoded compressed P-256 public key (33 bytes). Registered with the Coordination Node at onboarding. Used for signature verification of challenge tokens and receipts. **Privacy constraint:** This variable applies exclusively to Gateway and Guardian institutional keys. User and agent public keys must never appear in any shared data structure, token, or receipt (see [protocol.md](protocol.md) section 9).

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md), [guardian_role.md](../specs/guardian_role.md), [gateway_role.md](../specs/gateway_role.md), [cryptographic_operations_specification.md](../specs/cryptographic_operations_specification.md)
