### 4.6 Receipt and Signature Variables

Variables appearing in the completed trilateral receipt (the signed token retained by all three parties).

<details>
<summary><code>receipt_id</code> — string — Unique identifier for a completed receipt.</summary>

**Required.** UUID v7 format. Primary key in D1 receipt tables for both Gateway and Guardian. Used for receipt lookups, dispute resolution, and audit trails.

**Sources:** [receipt_format_and_assembly_specification.md](../specs/receipt_format_and_assembly_specification.md), [gateway_infrastructure.md](../specs/gateway_infrastructure.md) (D1 receipts), [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 receipts)

**Note:** Was missing from the previous glossary (adversarial review T-MAJ-2).
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>signatures</code> — object — Container for the three trilateral signatures.</summary>

**Required.** Object containing `service_gateway_sig`, `gateway_sig`, and `guardian_sig`. All three are present in every completed receipt.

**Sources:** [receipt_format_and_assembly_specification.md](../specs/receipt_format_and_assembly_specification.md)

**Open issue:** Triple vs dual signature structure needs resolution (adversarial review P-CRIT-2).
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>service_gateway_sig</code> — string — Service-side signature via the Gateway.</summary>

**Required in receipt.** Hex-encoded signature. The Gateway signs on behalf of the service (the service trusts its Gateway).

**Sources:** [receipt_format_and_assembly_specification.md](../specs/receipt_format_and_assembly_specification.md), [cryptographic_operations_specification.md](../specs/cryptographic_operations_specification.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>gateway_sig</code> — string — Gateway's independent signature on the receipt.</summary>

**Required in receipt.** Hex-encoded ECDSA P-256 signature. The Gateway signs as an independent party in the trilateral handshake.

**Sources:** [receipt_format_and_assembly_specification.md](../specs/receipt_format_and_assembly_specification.md), [cryptographic_operations_specification.md](../specs/cryptographic_operations_specification.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>guardian_sig</code> — string — Guardian's signature on the receipt (contains OOB proof).</summary>

**Required in receipt.** Hex-encoded ECDSA P-256 signature. The Guardian signs as the user's trusted party. The OOB proof is embedded inside the Guardian's signed payload.

**Sources:** [receipt_format_and_assembly_specification.md](../specs/receipt_format_and_assembly_specification.md), [cryptographic_operations_specification.md](../specs/cryptographic_operations_specification.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>receipt_json</code> — string (JSON) — Full serialized receipt stored in D1.</summary>

**Required.** The complete trilateral receipt as a JSON string. Stored for archival and dispute resolution.

**Sources:** [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 receipts), [gateway_infrastructure.md](../specs/gateway_infrastructure.md) (D1 receipts)
</details>

