### 4.7 Service Rule and Policy Variables

Variables used in the Gateway's and Guardian's policy evaluation engines for per-request attestation decisions.

<details>
<summary><code>rule_type</code> — string — Category of attestation rule.</summary>

**Required.** Classification for policy matching. Gateway values: `action`, `amount_threshold`, `jurisdiction`, `feature_category`, `time_based`, `default`. Guardian values: `attestation_override`, `pre_authorization`, `spending_threshold`.

**Sources:** [gateway_infrastructure.md](../specs/gateway_infrastructure.md) (D1 service_rules), [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 user_rules)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>conditions</code> — string (JSON) — Rule matching criteria.</summary>

**Required.** JSON-serialized object containing the conditions that trigger a rule (e.g., action name, amount threshold, jurisdiction, time window). Evaluated by the policy engine to determine if this rule applies to a given request.

**Sources:** [gateway_infrastructure.md](../specs/gateway_infrastructure.md) (D1 service_rules), [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 user_rules)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>attestation_level_override</code> — string — User-configured attestation level override.</summary>

**Optional.** In Guardian user rules, allows the user to raise the attestation requirement above the service's request. Must be >= `minimum_attestation_level`.

**Sources:** [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 user_rules)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>pre_authorized</code> — integer (boolean) — Whether to skip OOB for matching requests.</summary>

**Optional.** D1 integer flag (0/1). When 1, the Guardian signs without prompting the user for OOB, provided the request matches the rule's conditions. User-configured convenience setting.

**Sources:** [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 user_rules)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>priority</code> — integer — Rule evaluation precedence.</summary>

**Required.** Higher values are evaluated first. When multiple rules match a request, the highest-priority match wins.

**Sources:** [gateway_infrastructure.md](../specs/gateway_infrastructure.md) (D1 service_rules), [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 user_rules)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>enabled</code> — integer (boolean) — Whether a rule is active.</summary>

**Required.** D1 integer flag (0/1). Disabled rules are skipped during policy evaluation. Allows toggling rules without deleting them.

**Sources:** [gateway_infrastructure.md](../specs/gateway_infrastructure.md) (D1 service_rules), [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 user_rules)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>rule_id</code> — string — Unique identifier for an attestation rule within a rule set.</summary>

**Required.** snake_case, max 64 characters, pattern: `^[a-z][a-z0-9_]{0,63}$`. Must be unique within the rule set (service or Guardian). Reserved values: `default` (the implicit default rule when no other rule matches), `dynamic_override` (used in `applicable_rule` when a dynamic override was applied).

**Sources:** [attestation_rule_schema.md](../specs/attestation_rule_schema.md) (sections 2.1, 7.2, 8)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>rule_set_version</code> — integer — Monotonically increasing version of a service's rule set.</summary>

**Required in rule sets.** Starts at 1, incremented on any change to the rules array. Captured in the receipt via `applicable_rule` so auditors can verify which version of the rules was in effect. Null in `applicable_rule` for dynamic overrides (which are not part of the versioned set).

**Sources:** [attestation_rule_schema.md](../specs/attestation_rule_schema.md) (sections 2.2, 8)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>condition_field</code> / <code>field</code> — string — The request context field a rule condition evaluates.</summary>

**Required in conditions.** Standard fields: `action`, `amount`, `currency`, `feature`, `user_jurisdiction`, `service_jurisdiction`, `time_since_last_auth`. Services may define custom fields following snake_case convention.

**Sources:** [attestation_rule_schema.md](../specs/attestation_rule_schema.md) (sections 2.1, 3.1)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>condition_operator</code> / <code>operator</code> — string — The comparison operation in a rule condition.</summary>

**Required in conditions.** Enum: `eq`, `neq`, `gt`, `gte`, `lt`, `lte`, `in`, `not_in`, `exists`. Determines how the field value is compared against the condition's target value.

**Sources:** [attestation_rule_schema.md](../specs/attestation_rule_schema.md) (sections 2.1, 3.2)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>condition_value</code> / <code>value</code> — any — The target value in a rule condition.</summary>

**Required in conditions (except when operator is `exists`).** Type depends on operator: string or number for comparisons, array for `in`/`not_in`, boolean for `exists`.

**Sources:** [attestation_rule_schema.md](../specs/attestation_rule_schema.md) (sections 2.1, 3.2)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>dynamic_override</code> — boolean — Flag indicating a per-request attestation override from the service.</summary>

**Required in override objects, always `true`.** When present, the Gateway skips registered rule evaluation and uses the override's `attestation_level_required` directly (subject to floor enforcement).

**Sources:** [attestation_rule_schema.md](../specs/attestation_rule_schema.md) (section 2.3), [gateway_policy_evaluation_engine.md](../specs/gateway_policy_evaluation_engine.md) (section 2.2)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>always_require_approval</code> — boolean — Guardian rule flag forcing human involvement.</summary>

**Optional, default false.** When true on a Guardian rule, the Guardian always prompts the user for explicit approval even if the attestation requirement could be auto-satisfied by the agent. Forces `approval_source` to `user` in the receipt.

**Sources:** [attestation_rule_schema.md](../specs/attestation_rule_schema.md) (section 7.2)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>daily_spending_limit</code> — object — Guardian rule field capping daily authorized spend.</summary>

**Optional.** Contains `amount` (number) and `currency` (string, ISO 4217). If the cumulative authorized spend for a service would exceed this limit, the Guardian requires human approval regardless of other delegation rules.

**Sources:** [attestation_rule_schema.md](../specs/attestation_rule_schema.md) (section 7.2)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>blocked</code> — boolean — Guardian rule flag blocking all service authentication.</summary>

**Optional, default false.** When true, the Guardian refuses all authentication requests for the service. Reversible — the user can unblock later. The agent is notified when a service is blocked.

**Sources:** [attestation_rule_schema.md](../specs/attestation_rule_schema.md) (sections 7.2, 7.4)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>revoked</code> — boolean — Guardian action permanently removing a service account.</summary>

**Optional, default false.** When true, the Guardian permanently deletes the service account registration, cached manifest, and all associated Guardian rules. Irreversible — the agent must re-register from scratch. The agent is notified.

**Sources:** [attestation_rule_schema.md](../specs/attestation_rule_schema.md) (sections 7.2, 7.4)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>approval_source</code> — string — Whether the Guardian's approval was automatic or human-involved.</summary>

**Required in receipts.** Enum: `rule` (Guardian auto-approved per delegation policy, no human prompt) or `user` (human explicitly approved via OOB). Captures the provenance of the Guardian's signing decision.

**Sources:** [attestation_rule_schema.md](../specs/attestation_rule_schema.md) (section 7.5)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>approval_rule_description</code> — string — Human-readable description of the approval decision.</summary>

**Required in receipts.** If `approval_source` is `rule`: describes the delegation rule that allowed auto-approval (e.g., "Agent discretionary budget: auto-approve under $50/day"). If `approval_source` is `user`: contains the device used and timestamp of human approval (e.g., "Approved via iPhone 15 Pro at 2026-03-19T14:34:22Z").

**Sources:** [attestation_rule_schema.md](../specs/attestation_rule_schema.md) (section 7.5)
</details>

