### 4.8 Coordination Node Registry Variables

Variables stored in the Coordination Node's KV-backed registry and Merkle tree.

<details>
<summary><code>registered_at</code> — number — Unix timestamp (ms) of initial node registration.</summary>

**Required.** Set once at registration time. Immutable.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md), [gateway_infrastructure.md](../specs/gateway_infrastructure.md) (D1), [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>last_updated</code> — number — Unix timestamp (ms) of last record modification.</summary>

**Required.** Updated on any change to the node record (key rotation, status change, metadata update).

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md), [gateway_infrastructure.md](../specs/gateway_infrastructure.md) (D1), [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>previous_keys</code> — array of objects — Historical key rotation records.</summary>

**Optional.** Array of `{public_key, rotated_at, reason}` objects. Maintained for backward verification of receipts signed with older keys during transition windows.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>merkle_leaf_hash</code> — string — SHA-256 hash of this node's leaf in the Merkle tree.</summary>

**Required.** Computed from the canonical serialization of the node record. Used for inclusion proofs.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>merkle_root</code> — string — Current Merkle tree root hash (SHA-256, hex).</summary>

**Required.** The global registry integrity proof. Recomputed on every registration, revocation, or key rotation.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)

**Related:** `leaf_count`, `registry_version`, `computed_at`
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>registry_version</code> — number — Monotonically increasing counter for registry modifications.</summary>

**Required.** Incremented on every write operation. Used for consistency checks and stale-cache detection.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>leaf_count</code> — number — Number of leaf nodes in the Merkle tree.</summary>

**Required.** Total registered nodes (active + deprecated). Used for tree structure calculations.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>computed_at</code> — number — Unix timestamp when the Merkle root was last computed.</summary>

**Required.** Freshness indicator for the Merkle root.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>root_public_key</code> — string — Coordination Node's Master Root Key (public).</summary>

**Required.** Used to verify Coordination Node signatures on registry responses. Subject to its own rotation lifecycle.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>signing_key_version</code> — number — Which root key version signed this response.</summary>

**Required in lookup responses.** Allows verifiers to select the correct root public key during key rotation transitions.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>valid_from</code> — timestamp — When a rotated key becomes active.</summary>

**Required for key rotation.** ISO 8601 timestamp. During the transition window, both old and new keys are valid.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md), [key_rotation_and_lifecycle_management.md](../specs/key_rotation_and_lifecycle_management.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>valid_until</code> — timestamp — When an old key stops being accepted.</summary>

**Required for key rotation.** ISO 8601 timestamp marking end of key validity. After this time, signatures using the old key are rejected.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md), [key_rotation_and_lifecycle_management.md](../specs/key_rotation_and_lifecycle_management.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>registered_by</code> — string — DID of entity that registered a node.</summary>

**Required.** Governance audit trail. Records which administrator or governance body approved a Gateway or Guardian registration.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>leaf_index</code> — integer — Position of node's leaf in Merkle tree.</summary>

**Required.** Zero-indexed position in the Coordination Node's Merkle tree. Used with `leaf_hash` and `merkle_root` for inclusion proofs.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>leaf_hash</code> — string — SHA-256 hash of the leaf at this position.</summary>

**Required.** Hash of the node's registration data at `leaf_index`. Used in Merkle inclusion proofs.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)

**Related:** `merkle_leaf_hash`, `merkle_root`, `leaf_index`
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>published_at</code> — timestamp — When a root key version was published.</summary>

**Required.** ISO 8601 timestamp. Records when the Coordination Node made a new signing key version available.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>signed_at</code> — timestamp — When a coordination transaction was signed.</summary>

**Required.** ISO 8601 timestamp recorded by the Coordination Node at signing time.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>txn_hash</code> — string — Hash of a coordination transaction.</summary>

**Required.** SHA-256 hash of the serialized coordination transaction. Used for integrity verification and audit trail.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>coordination_node_did</code> — string — DID of the signing coordination node.</summary>

**Required.** Identifies which Coordination Node signed a particular transaction or lookup response.

**Sources:** [coordination_node_data_model.md](../specs/coordination_node_data_model.md)
</details>

