### 4.10 Device Binding and OOB Variables

Variables used in device registration, OOB notification, and the OOB approval/rejection flow.

<details>
<summary><code>device_id</code> — string — Unique identifier for a registered OOB device.</summary>

**Required.** Primary key in Guardian's D1 `devices` table. Identifies a user's phone, hardware key, or other OOB-capable device.

**Sources:** [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 devices), [oob_notification_protocol_specification.md](../specs/oob_notification_protocol_specification.md), [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>device_name</code> — string — Human-readable name for the device.</summary>

**Optional.** User-facing label (e.g., "iPhone 15", "YubiKey 5"). Shown in device management UI and OOB prompts.

**Sources:** [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 devices)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>device_public_key</code> — string — Public key from a registered OOB device.</summary>

**Required for device_signature OOB.** Used by the Guardian to verify device signatures during `device_signature` OOB authentication. Stored in the Guardian's D1; never exposed in tokens or receipts (privacy constraint).

**Sources:** [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 devices), [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>device_type</code> — string — Category of OOB device.</summary>

**Required.** One of: `mobile`, `desktop`, `hardware_key`. Determines available OOB methods and notification channels.

**Sources:** [guardian_infrastructure.md](../specs/guardian_infrastructure.md) (D1 devices)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>txn_id</code> — string — Transaction identifier for an OOB request.</summary>

**Required.** Unique per-OOB-request. Used by Durable Objects to coordinate the MCP-to-REST bridge: agent initiates via MCP, user approves/rejects via REST, DO correlates both using `txn_id`.

**Sources:** [oob_notification_protocol_specification.md](../specs/oob_notification_protocol_specification.md), [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>display_text</code> — string — Text shown to the user in OOB prompts.</summary>

**Required.** Human-readable description of what the user is being asked to approve (e.g., "Authorize booking at Acme Travel for $500").

**Sources:** [oob_notification_protocol_specification.md](../specs/oob_notification_protocol_specification.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>push_token</code> — string — APNs or FCM token for push notifications.</summary>

**Optional.** Used to send OOB notifications to the user's device. Stored in Guardian D1; refreshed on device check-in.

**Sources:** [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>bind_id</code> — string — Binding ceremony identifier.</summary>

**Required during device onboarding.** Unique ID for the device binding process. Used to correlate the QR code/NFC invitation with the device's registration response.

**Sources:** [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>device_platform</code> — string — OS platform of a registered device.</summary>

**Optional.** Finer granularity than `device_type`. Values: `ios`, `android`, etc. `device_type` captures category (mobile/desktop/hardware_key); `device_platform` captures the specific OS.

**Sources:** [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>bound_at</code> — timestamp — When device binding ceremony completed.</summary>

**Required.** ISO 8601 timestamp recorded in the device record upon successful binding.

**Sources:** [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>last_seen_at</code> — timestamp — Last device check-in or signature activity.</summary>

**Optional.** Updated on each device interaction. Used for staleness detection and device management.

**Sources:** [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>revocation_reason</code> — string — Human-readable reason for device revocation.</summary>

**Required on revocation.** Stored in the device record when a device is revoked. Distinct from bare `reason` in coordination node context.

**Sources:** [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>signature_count</code> — integer — Cumulative signatures produced by this device.</summary>

**Optional.** Running counter for audit and anomaly detection purposes.

**Sources:** [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>push_failures</code> — integer — Consecutive failed push notification attempts.</summary>

**Optional.** Used to detect unresponsive devices. May trigger fallback to alternative OOB methods after threshold.

**Sources:** [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>attestation_verified</code> — boolean — Whether device hardware attestation was verified during binding.</summary>

**Optional.** True if the Guardian verified hardware attestation (e.g., Apple DeviceCheck, Android SafetyNet) during the binding ceremony.

**Sources:** [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>attestation_verified_at</code> — timestamp — When device attestation was last verified.</summary>

**Optional.** ISO 8601 timestamp. May differ from `bound_at` if attestation is re-verified periodically.

**Sources:** [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>max_attempts</code> — integer — Maximum allowed binding ceremony attempts before lockout.</summary>

**Required.** Security control to prevent brute-force binding attacks.

**Sources:** [device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md](../docs/device_binding_and_onboarding_ceremony.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>failed_attempts</code> — integer — Number of failed binding attempts so far.</summary>

