</details>

<details>
<summary><code>retryable</code> — boolean — Whether the client should retry.</summary>

**Required.** When true, the error is transient and the client should retry (possibly after a delay). When false, retrying with the same parameters will produce the same error.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>after_seconds</code> — integer — Suggested retry delay.</summary>

**Optional.** Only meaningful when `retryable` is true. Recommended number of seconds the client should wait before retrying.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>request_id</code> — string — Unique identifier for the request.</summary>

**Required.** Generated by the responding node. Used for debugging, support tickets, and audit log correlation.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md)
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_SIGNATURE_INVALID</code> — error code — Cryptographic signature verification failed.</summary>

**HTTP 401.** A signature in the handshake flow (Gateway signature on challenge, Guardian signature on response, or manifest signature) failed verification. The receiving party could not verify the signature using the expected public key. Not retryable — indicates a cryptographic integrity issue, key mismatch, or payload tampering. Service may trigger this if it validates receipt signatures.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [cryptographic_operations_specification.md](../specs/cryptographic_operations_specification.md)

**Related:** `UNS_MANIFEST_SIGNATURE_INVALID`, `UNS_SUSPECT_SIGNATURE`, `manifest_signature`, `gateway_sig`, `guardian_sig`
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_NOT_FOUND</code> — error code — The service could not find an account for the given <code>service_account_id</code>.</summary>

**HTTP 404.** Returned by the Gateway when the Gateway-service callback fails because the service cannot locate the claimed account. Not retryable with the same `service_account_id` — the agent should investigate (account may have been deleted at the service, or the stored `service_account_id` may be stale).

**Sources:** [mcp_tool_definitions.md](../specs/mcp_tool_definitions.md) section 2.4, [gateway_role.md](../specs/gateway_role.md) section 4.3
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_SERVICE_CALLBACK_TIMEOUT</code> — error code — Service callback did not respond within the configured timeout window.</summary>

**HTTP 503.** The Gateway invoked the service's callback endpoint but received no response within the timeout (default 10 seconds). Nonce is NOT consumed — the agent may retry `submit_signed_token` with the same payload. Retryable.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [gateway_role.md](../specs/gateway_role.md) section 4.3.6
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_SERVICE_CALLBACK_ERROR</code> — error code — Service callback returned a server error or malformed response.</summary>

**HTTP 502.** The service callback endpoint returned HTTP 5xx or an unparseable response. Nonce is NOT consumed — the agent may retry. Retryable.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [gateway_role.md](../specs/gateway_role.md) section 4.3.6
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_SERVICE_CALLBACK_INVALID</code> — error code — Service deliberately rejected the authentication via callback.</summary>

**HTTP 403.** The service returned HTTP 4xx, indicating a policy decision (e.g., user banned, account suspended). Nonce IS consumed. Not retryable.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [gateway_role.md](../specs/gateway_role.md) section 4.3.6
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_MISMATCH</code> — error code — Service returned a different <code>service_account_id</code> than previously recorded.</summary>

**HTTP 409.** On subsequent handshakes, the service must return the same `service_account_id` for the same user. A mismatch indicates a service bug, account migration, or security issue. Gateway rejects and logs as security incident. Not retryable.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [gateway_role.md](../specs/gateway_role.md) section 4.3.5a
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_ACCOUNT_CREATION_RATE_LIMITED</code> — error code — Too many null-account handshakes for this Guardian + service pair.</summary>

**HTTP 429.** Repeated first-handshake attempts (where `service_account_id` is null) from the same Guardian for the same service. Default limit: 3 per hour. Retryable after the rate limit window resets.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [gateway_role.md](../specs/gateway_role.md) section 4.3.8
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_NONCE_EXPIRED</code> — error code — The nonce has exceeded its TTL (5 minutes) and is no longer valid.</summary>

**HTTP 410 (Gone).** The nonce was valid when issued but has expired before the Guardian's signed response was submitted. Not retryable with the same nonce — the agent must re-initiate the handshake by calling `get_uns_challenge` again. Nonce is NOT consumed (it no longer exists in KV).

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [gateway_infrastructure.md](../specs/gateway_infrastructure.md) section 4.4

**Related:** `nonce`, `UNS_NONCE_REPLAY`
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_SERVICE_NOT_REGISTERED</code> — error code — The requested service is not hosted by this Gateway.</summary>

**HTTP 404.** The `service_name` in the request does not match any service registered with this Gateway. Not retryable against this Gateway — the agent should verify the `gateway_id` and `service_name` from the Guardian's cached manifest.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [gateway_policy_evaluation_engine.md](../specs/gateway_policy_evaluation_engine.md)

**Related:** `service_name`, `gateway_id`
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_MANIFEST_CHANGED</code> — error code — The service manifest has been updated since the Guardian last cached it.</summary>

**HTTP 409 (Conflict).** The `manifest_version` in the Guardian's cached manifest does not match the current version at the Gateway. The Guardian should call `refetch_manifest` to update its cache before retrying. Retryable after manifest refresh.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [guardian_mcp_tool_definitions.md](../specs/guardian_mcp_tool_definitions.md) section 3.3

**Related:** `manifest_version`, `manifest_issued_at`, `manifest_signature`
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_DYNAMIC_OVERRIDE_BELOW_FLOOR</code> — error code — A dynamic attestation override attempted to set the requirement below the service's minimum.</summary>

**HTTP 400 (Bad Request).** The service sent a dynamic override with an `attestation_level_required` that is weaker than the `minimum_attestation_level` declared in the service manifest. The Gateway rejects the override. Not retryable with the same override value — the service must send a valid attestation level at or above the floor.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [gateway_policy_evaluation_engine.md](../specs/gateway_policy_evaluation_engine.md)

**Related:** `minimum_attestation_level`, `attestation_level_required`, `applicable_rule`
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_GUARDIAN_UNAVAILABLE</code> — error code — The Guardian is unreachable or in maintenance mode.</summary>

**HTTP 503 (Service Unavailable).** The Gateway cannot contact the Guardian, or the Coordination Node indicates the Guardian's status is `maintenance`. Returned by the Gateway when it detects the Guardian is temporarily unavailable. Nonce is NOT consumed. Retryable after waiting for the Guardian to recover.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [gateway_policy_evaluation_engine.md](../specs/gateway_policy_evaluation_engine.md) section 7

**Related:** `guardian_id`, `endpoint_url`, `status`
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_INTERNAL_ERROR</code> — error code — An unrecoverable internal infrastructure error occurred.</summary>

**HTTP 500 (Internal Server Error).** Generic error returned by Gateway or Guardian when an internal failure prevents completing the handshake. Common causes: policy evaluation engine crash, database connectivity loss, malformed rule configuration, or unexpected exception. Nonce is NOT consumed (error occurred during processing without nonce consumption). Retryable with exponential backoff after waiting.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [guardian_policy_evaluation_engine.md](../specs/guardian_policy_evaluation_engine.md) section 7, [gateway_policy_evaluation_engine.md](../specs/gateway_policy_evaluation_engine.md) section 7

**Related:** `UNS_STORAGE_UNAVAILABLE`, error handling best practices
</details>

<details>
<summary><code>UNS_STORAGE_UNAVAILABLE</code> — error code — Database, KV store, or Durable Object is temporarily unreachable.</summary>

**HTTP 503 (Service Unavailable).** Returned by Gateway or Guardian when D1, KV, or Durable Objects become temporarily unavailable (connection timeout, rate limit, backoff state). More specific than `UNS_INTERNAL_ERROR` when the cause is explicitly an infrastructure storage system. Nonce is NOT consumed (error prevented storage update). Retryable with exponential backoff.

**Sources:** [error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md](../specs/error_code_catalog_and_response_specification.md), [guardian_policy_evaluation_engine.md](../specs/guardian_policy_evaluation_engine.md) section 7, [gateway_policy_evaluation_engine.md](../specs/gateway_policy_evaluation_engine.md) section 7

**Related:** `UNS_INTERNAL_ERROR`, `UNS_SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE`
</details>

